With the sluggish economy, high unemployment and ailing State-Owned Entities many south Africans are hoping Mboweni will offer some reprieve this Wednesday. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Tito Mboweni delivered his Budget Speech on Wednesday. With the sluggish economy, high unemployment and ailing State-Owned Entities many south Africans are hoping Mboweni will offer some reprieve. President Cyril Ramaphosa has said the Finance Minister will deliver a "robust budget with lots of good news". Ramaphosa has acknowledged that while it’s set to be a difficult balancing act, the budget will meet expectations.